    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-05T11:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-05T11:16:00-05:00" n="609"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1239</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-05T12:00:00-04:16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1918, noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My January 12, 1 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d609fn1">Not printed.</note> and
                    January 25, 6 p.m. The President received the Mexican mission in farewell
                    audience yesterday. <hi rend="italic">La Nacion</hi> of today states that
                        <persName corresp="#p_ECM1">Cabrera</persName> will visit Paraguay and will
                    then return to Argentine where he will visit the central and western provinces
                    and that he will then visit Chile, Peru and Bolivia. It further states that one
                    delegate, General Montes, will visit Chile and supposed another, Ugarte,
                    Ecuador. [E. Hidalgo?] will visit Brazil. The Mexican mission has not been
                    received at any diplomatic functions and none of the mission has called at this
                    Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
